recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2015-2019 Ford F-150 and 2017-2019 Ford F-250 Super Duty, F-350 Super Duty, F-450 Super Duty, and F-550 Super Duty pick-up trucks equipped with an engine block heater.   Water and contaminants may get into the block heater cable's splice connector causing corrosion and damage.
recalls.Consequence: When the heater is plugged in, prolonged corrosion could cause a resistive short, increasing the risk of overheated or melted wiring which can increase the risk of a fire.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will disable the block heater cable, free of charge.  Once parts are available, Dealers will replace the engine block heater cable, free of charge.  The recall began June 3, 2019.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 18S45.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2015-2019 Ford F-150 and 2017-2019 Ford F-250 Super Duty, F-350 Super Duty, F-450 Super Duty, and F-550 Super Duty pick-up trucks equipped with an engine block heater and previously remedied under recall 18V894.   During the previous repair, the block heater cable's splice connector may have been damaged.
recalls.Consequence: A damaged cable could cause a resistive short, increasing the risk of overheated or melted wiring, increasing the risk of a fire.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will disable the engine block heater from being used.  When replacement cables become available, a second notice will be mailed and dealers will replace the engine block heater cord, free of charge.  The recall began May 31, 2019.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 19S11.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2015-2018 Ford F-150 Regular Cab and SuperCrew Cab vehicles.  If a front seat belt pretensioner deploys as the result of a crash, the sparks may ignite materials such as carpeting or insulation within the B-pillar area.
recalls.Consequence: A vehicle fire could result if materials ignite inside the vehicle.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will remove the B-pillar insulation material and wiring harness tape, and install heat resistant tape, free of charge. The recall began September 28, 2018.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 18S27.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2015-2017 Ford F-150, and 2017 F-250, F-350, F-450, and F-550 Super Duty trucks.  The doors on these vehicles may have a bent or kinked actuation cable or the door latches may freeze after water gets into the latch.  Either condition can result in the doors opening while driving although they appear to be closed.
recalls.Consequence: A door that opens while driving can increase the risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will inspect the door latch actuation cables and repair if necessary, and install water shields over the door latches, free of charge.  The recall began October 12, 2018.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 17S33.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2015-2017 F-150, and 2017 F-250 and F-350 trucks equipped with a crew cab.  The left rear inflatable seat belt buckle assembly may be inadequately attached to its mounting bracket.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) number 210, "Seat Belt Assembly Anchorages."
recalls.Consequence: If the left rear inflatable seat belt buckle separates from it's mounting bracket, the seat occupant may not be adequately restrained, increasing their risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will inspect the seat belt assembly, replacing the attaching rivet as necessary, free of charge.  Interim notices informing owners of the safety risk were mailed October 18, 2017.  Owners will receive a second notice when the remedy becomes available.  Owners may contact Ford Customer Service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 17C12.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2015-2017 F-150, and 2017 F-250, F-350, F-450, and F-550 vehicles originally produced with black or body colored exterior door handles that may have been subsequently equipped with a chrome exterior door handle cover accessory kit purchased from a Ford dealer.  These accessory door handle covers may cause the doors to unlatch in a side impact collision.  As such, these vehicles may fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) number 206, "Door Locks and Door Retention Components."
recalls.Consequence: If the doors unlatch and open in a side impact collision, the occupants have an increased risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will remove the accessory covers and refund the purchase price.  The recall began July 13, 2017.  Owners may contact Ford at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for the recall is 17C09.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain model year 2015 Ford F-150 SuperCrew trucks manufactured January 22, 2015, to March 17, 2015.  The affected vehicles may be equipped with driver or front passenger seat belt anchorage assemblies whose pretensioner cable was not properly crimped.  As a result, the seat belts may not properly restrain the seat occupant in the event of a crash.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) number 209, "Seat Belt Assemblies" and 210, " Seat Belt Assembly Anchorages."
recalls.Consequence: An occupant that is not be properly restrained is at an increased risk of injury in the event of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will replace the driver and/or front passenger side seat belt retractor(s) and pretensioner(s), free of charge.  The recall began on February 12, 2016.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 15C17.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Component: FORWARD COLLISION AVOIDANCE: ADAPTIVE CRUISE CONTROL
recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain model year 2015 Ford F-150 trucks manufactured March 18, 2014, to August 6, 2015 and equipped with Adaptive Cruise Control (ACC).  While using the Adaptive Cruise Control, the vehicle may falsely detect an obstacle in its path and may unexpectedly apply the brakes.
recalls.Consequence: A vehicle that unexpectedly brakes increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will reprogram the cruise control module with updated ACC radar software, free of charge.  The recall began on October 25, 2015.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 15S29.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain model year 2015 Ford F-150 vehicles manufactured January 30, 2015, to January 31, 2015.  The affected vehicles may have loose or missing underbody heat shields.
recalls.Consequence: A missing underbody heat shield can lead to degradation or melting of the fuel or vapor lines, increasing the risk of a fire.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will inspect the vehicle for missing underbody heat shields and fasteners, and will install the missing components as required, free of charge.  The recall began on May 13, 2015.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 15S12.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain model year 2015 Ford F-150 trucks manufactured March 19, 2015, to March 30, 2015.  The affected vehicles may have been built with a steering upper intermediate shaft that was improperly riveted.
recalls.Consequence: If the intermediate shaft was improperly riveted, it could separate from the intermediate shaft flex coupling, resulting in a loss of steering control and increasing the risk of a vehicle crash.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will inspect the intermediate shaft and replace it, as necessary, free of charge. The recall began on May 22, 2015.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 15S17.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2015-2016 F-150 pick-up trucks equipped with 3.5L GTDI engines and block immersion heaters that were potentially relocated from their originally installed location.  The incorrect location could put the heater too close to hot engine components, possibly resulting in a damaged cable.
recalls.Consequence: A damaged cable could cause a resistive short, increasing the risk of overheated or melted wiring, increasing the risk of a fire.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will inspect the block heater's location and its cable, replacing components as necessary, free of charge.  If the replacement parts are not available, dealers will disable the existing block heater cable from being used until parts become available.  The recall began April 9, 2020.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 20S08.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2014-2017 F-150 pickup trucks equipped with 3.5L Ecoboost engines.  The brake master cylinder may leak brake fluid into the brake booster.
recalls.Consequence: A loss of brake fluid may result in a change in brake pedal travel and feel, increased pedal effort and reduced front brake function, possibly requiring greater effort and distance to stop the vehicle.  These conditions can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will replace the brake master cylinder and inspect the brake booster, replacing it as necessary, free of charge.  Ford issued owners an interim notification on June 30, 2020.  The recall began on October 28, 2020.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 20S31.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Tenneco Automotive (DRiV) is recalling certain MOOG K500359 ball joints, for aftermarket installation on 2015-2018 Ford F-150 trucks.  The ball joint may have a misaligned dust boot and may be missing alignment hole and installation warning tag, which may lead to improper alignment of the ball joint.
recalls.Consequence: An incorrectly installed ball joint may cause the ball joint stud to break, which can compromise front wheel control, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: DRiV will notify owners, and dealers will inspect, and if necessary replace the ball joint, free of charge.  Owner letters were mailed May 5, 2021.  Owners may contact Tenneco Automotive customer service at 1-877-489-6659.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

issues.title: IWE (Integrated Wheel End) Hub Failure
issues.description: The Integrated Wheel End (IWE) system used in 4WD F-150s fails, causing grinding noises, vibration, and potential loss of 4WD functionality. The vacuum-operated system that engages/disengages the front wheels often malfunctions due to vacuum leaks or internal component failure.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty IWE actuators, repair vacuum lines, or convert to manual locking hubs
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of vacuum lines, avoid extended periods in 4WD on dry pavement

issues.title: Cam Phaser Failure (3.5L EcoBoost)
issues.description: The 3.5L EcoBoost V6 engines experience cam phaser failures, causing rattling noises on startup and potential catastrophic engine damage if not addressed. The timing chain tensioners and phasers wear prematurely.
issues.fix_description: Replace cam phasers, timing chains, tensioners, and related components
issues.prevention: Use recommended oil viscosity, frequent oil changes, avoid extended idle periods

issues.title: Turbocharger Failure (EcoBoost Engines)
issues.description: Both 2.7L and 3.5L EcoBoost engines suffer from premature turbocharger failures, including wastegate actuator problems, bearing failures, and oil leaks into the intercooler system.
issues.fix_description: Replace failed turbocharger assembly, clean intercooler system, replace contaminated oil
issues.prevention: Allow proper warm-up and cool-down periods, use high-quality oil, regular maintenance

issues.title: Transmission Shudder (10R80 10-Speed)
issues.description: The 10R80 10-speed automatic transmission experiences shuddering, harsh shifting, and hesitation, particularly during light acceleration and low speeds. TSB updates include software calibrations and torque converter replacement.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, transmission fluid change, torque converter replacement if needed
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, avoid aggressive driving habits

issues.title: Water Pump Failure (5.0L V8)
issues.description: The 5.0L Coyote V8 engines experience premature water pump failures, leading to coolant leaks and potential overheating. The plastic impeller can fail, causing loss of coolant circulation.
issues.fix_description: Replace water pump, thermostat, and coolant. Inspect for head gasket damage
issues.prevention: Regular coolant system maintenance, monitor coolant levels, address leaks promptly

issues.title: Spark Plug Ejection (5.4L Triton)
issues.description: The 5.4L Triton V8 (available in early 2015 models) has insufficient thread engagement for spark plugs, causing them to blow out of the cylinder head, resulting in loss of compression and expensive repairs.
issues.fix_description: Thread repair insert installation, cylinder head repair or replacement
issues.prevention: Use proper torque specifications, avoid over-tightening spark plugs

issues.title: Exhaust Manifold Cracking (5.0L V8)
issues.description: The 5.0L V8 engines develop cracks in the exhaust manifolds, particularly on the passenger side, causing exhaust leaks and ticking noises that worsen over time.
issues.fix_description: Replace cracked exhaust manifold, install updated design if available
issues.prevention: Allow proper warm-up periods, avoid rapid temperature changes

issues.title: HVAC Blend Door Actuator Failure
issues.description: The HVAC system blend door actuators fail frequently, causing clicking noises and inability to control air temperature or direction properly. Multiple actuators may fail simultaneously.
issues.fix_description: Replace failed blend door actuator(s), calibrate HVAC system
issues.prevention: Avoid forcing climate controls, perform regular HVAC system checks

issues.title: Rear Differential Leak
issues.description: Rear differentials, particularly in trucks with electronic locking differentials, develop leaks at the pinion seal and cover gasket, leading to gear oil loss and potential differential damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace pinion seal, cover gasket, and differential fluid
issues.prevention: Regular differential service, avoid overloading, inspect for leaks regularly

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: In-tank fuel pumps fail prematurely, causing fuel delivery issues, stalling, and no-start conditions. The issue is more common in trucks with higher mileage or contaminated fuel systems.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump assembly, clean fuel tank if contaminated
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, keep fuel tank above quarter full, replace fuel filter regularly

issues.title: Brake Booster Vacuum Leak
issues.description: Brake booster develops vacuum leaks, causing hard brake pedal, reduced braking assist, and potential safety concerns. The issue is often related to diaphragm failure inside the booster.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake booster assembly, check vacuum lines
issues.prevention: Regular brake system inspection, avoid harsh braking when possible

issues.title: Starter Motor Failure
issues.description: Starter motors fail prematurely, particularly in trucks with remote start systems or frequent stop-start cycles. The solenoid contacts wear out, causing intermittent or complete starting failure.
symptoms: Dashboard lights dim during start attempt
issues.fix_description: Replace starter motor assembly, check battery and charging system
issues.prevention: Maintain battery health, avoid excessive use of remote start

editorial.hero_blurb: The 3.5L EcoBoost F-150 rewrote the truck playbook, proving that twin turbos could deliver V8 power with V6 efficiency. This isn't just a work truckit's a high-tech hauler that dominates at the dragstrip and the job site.
editorial.essence: Ford's EcoBoost revolution began here, cramming 365-450hp and massive torque into America's best-selling truck. It proved that forced induction could replace displacement without sacrificing the grunt that truck buyers demand.
editorial.heritage: Building on F-Series DNA dating back to 1948, the 2015-2020 generation marked Ford's bold bet on turbocharged efficiency over traditional V8 muscle, fundamentally changing pickup expectations.
editorial.design_philosophy: Engineers prioritized real-world capability over engine displacement prejudice, creating a powerplant that could out-tow V8s while sipping fuel during daily commutes.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not directly race-bred, the EcoBoost engine architecture proved its mettle in Ford GT supercars and became a favorite among drag racers seeking boost-friendly modifications.
editorial.engine_character: Delivers immediate, explosive torque that hits like a freight train from 2,500 RPM, with turbos spooling up eagerly and pulling hard through the mid-range before tapering off at redline.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 6-speed automatic shifts decisively under power but can hunt for gears during light throttle operation, while the available 10-speed (2017+) provides seamless, almost imperceptible shifts.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Surprisingly composed for a full-size truck, with well-controlled body roll and confident highway manners, though the rear can get light under aggressive acceleration when unloaded.
editorial.steering_feel: Electrically-assisted steering offers good road feedback for its class, with appropriate weight buildup and decent precision, though it lacks the raw connection of older hydraulic systems.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, progressive braking with good pedal feel and impressive stopping power for such a large vehicle, especially when properly equipped for towing heavy loads.
editorial.sound_signature: Subdued but purposeful rumble at idle builds to an aggressive whoosh under boost, with turbo whistle becoming prominent during hard accelerationdistinctly modern and tech-forward.
editorial.ideal_owner: Performance-minded truck buyers who want both weekend capability and weekday efficiency, plus anyone who needs serious towing power without V8 fuel consumption.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Traditional V8 purists who prioritize engine note over capability, or buyers seeking maximum simplicity and long-term durability over cutting-edge technology.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for 2017+ models with the 10-speed transmission for optimal refinement, and budget for premium fuel to unlock full performance potential. These trucks offer genuine performance credentials wrapped in everyday usability.

expertReviews.title: 2026 Ford F-150 Review: The Ultimate Truck Just Got Better!
pros: Multiple powertrain options including 700+ hp Raptor R and 400+ mile electric version
Major tech upgrade with 15-inch touchscreen and sync 5 system
Best-in-class towing capacity up to 14,000 lbs and enhanced trailer assist features
expertReviews.verdict: The 2026 Ford F-150 represents a revolutionary upgrade rather than just an incremental improvement. With extensive powertrain options from efficient hybrid to 700+ horsepower V8 to long-range electric, cutting-edge technology including hands-free BlueCruise 2, and class-leading towing capability, Ford continues to set the standard for modern trucks across all price points from $40,000 to $95,000.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Ford F-150 Review  Real Test Drive, Features & Power
pros: Multiple powerful engine options including hybrid
Over 13,000 lb towing capacity
Luxury-level interior refinement with premium materials
Advanced SYNC5 infotainment with 12-inch touchscreen
Pro Power Onboard system up to 7.2 kW
Comprehensive Ford Co-Pilot 360 2.0 safety suite
Impressive fuel efficiency up to 25 MPG combined with hybrid
Smart bed features with improved lighting and workbench tailgate
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Ford F-150 is described as a smart, strong, and stylish truck that successfully combines capability with advanced technology. With multiple engine options, impressive towing capacity, luxury interior features, and innovative utility like Pro Power Onboard, it's positioned as an excellent choice for both work and recreation. The reviewer concludes it absolutely deserves serious consideration for anyone upgrading or buying their first full-size pickup.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Ford F-150 | Honest Review and 0-60
pros: Excellent visibility with large windows
Top safety pick rating with 5-star crash test
Spacious interior with generous rear seat room
400 lb-ft torque from 2.7L twin turbo EcoBoost
Substantial storage throughout cabin and bed
High payload capacity of 1,600 lbs
Up to 800 miles range with conservative driving
cons: No proximity key features for $50k price point
Gas door doesn't lock when vehicle is locked
No wheel well liners in rear
Lower trim materials feel cheaper
Tailgate drops hard without dampening
No spray-in bed liner included
Large size may not fit in average garages
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 F-150 STX offers solid truck capability with excellent safety ratings and impressive visibility, but at $51k as tested, it lacks some expected premium features like proximity entry. The 2.7L EcoBoost provides good performance with 400 lb-ft torque, and the spacious cabin offers excellent utility. However, buyers should consider the substantial size and missing convenience features at this price point.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Ford F-150 XLT Powerboost Review and Off-Road Test
pros: 7.2 kW Pro Power system provides mobile power station capability
430 hp and 570 lb-ft torque from hybrid powertrain
Excellent interior space and storage in crew cab
Responsive Sync 4 infotainment with wireless CarPlay/Android Auto
Blue Cruise hands-free driving capability
Comfortable ride quality and good visibility
Fold-down desk option for mobile office use
cons: Fabric seats at this price point ($70k+)
Leaf springs create bouncy ride without payload
Automatic 4WD requires upgrade to Lariat trim
Price easily escalates with options
20-inch wheels prone to scratching
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 F-150 XLT with PowerBoost hybrid offers impressive capability with 430hp and useful 7.2kW onboard power, but at $70k with options, the Lariat trim offers better value. The hybrid system proves hybrids can be both efficient and powerful.

expertReviews.title: Here's What 2 Years With The New F-150 Has Been Like
pros: Pro Power on board system enables powering equipment at remote filming/racing sites
Excellent fuel economy with 1000km range per tank
Very comfortable for long drives - can drive 1000 miles without fatigue
Quick acceleration with hybrid turbocharged V6
Good winter capability with full-time four-wheel drive
Improved ride quality with retuned dampers
Excellent towing capacity - handles 22-foot car hauler with race car without complaint
cons: Pro Power system occasionally fails and can damage sensitive electronics like expensive filming lights
Multiple hybrid system failures requiring dealer visits and manual battery resets
Security vulnerabilities - broken into twice despite aftermarket bed cover
Reliability issues with complete system brick requiring battery disconnect
Color choice turned out to be extremely common despite appearing unique
expertReviews.verdict: After 33,000 kilometers over 2 years, the F-150 Lariat Power Boost has been 'fine' rather than excellent. While it excels at core truck duties like towing and long-distance comfort, reliability issues with the hybrid system and Pro Power feature have been frustrating. The reviewers appreciate its capability but wouldn't buy the same high-trim version again, preferring to save money and use portable generators instead. Despite issues, they remain endeared to it as their workhorse support vehicle.

expertReviews.title: Ford F150 - Our Next Tow Rig? Test Drive, Specs and Price
pros: Excellent towing capability
Very spacious interior with lots of leg room and storage
Twin turbo V6 petrol engine with good power delivery
Premium features like 360 surround sound and wireless charging
Dual fuel tanks with 120L capacity for ~1000km range
5-year unlimited kilometer warranty
Advanced trailer assist technology
Multiple drive modes including 4x4 capability
cons: Limited off-road capability due to longer wheelbase
No rear diff lock on Lariat trim (only on XLT)
No diesel engine option in Australia
Much larger size makes it less maneuverable than Ranger
Significantly more expensive than XLT model
XLT has smaller infotainment screen
expertReviews.verdict: The Ford F-150 is positioned as a premium towing vehicle that significantly outperforms the Ranger in hauling capability and interior space. While it sacrifices off-road agility due to its larger size and longer wheelbase, it excels as a luxury tow rig with advanced features, dual fuel tanks, and impressive power delivery. The reviewer acknowledges it would be a major upgrade for towing but remains uncertain about switching due to their mixed use requirements including off-road adventures where the Ranger remains superior.
